contentrichtext.text: {{Wiktionary|Jabberwock|Jabberwocky|jabberwocky}} {{TOCright}} '''"[[Jabberwocky]]"''' is an 1872 nonsense poem by Lewis Carroll, about an encounter between a young boy and a monster called the Jabberwock. '''Jabberwocky''' or '''Jabberwock''' may also refer to: ==Films and television== * [[Jabberwocky (film)|''Jabberwocky'' (1977 film)]], directed by Terry Gilliam * [[Jabberwocky (1971 film)|''Jabberwocky'' (1971 film)]], directed by Jan Švankmajer * [[Jabberwocky (TV series)|''Jabberwocky'' (TV series)]], (1972–1974) * ''Jabberwock'', 2010 television movie directed by [[Steven R. Monroe]] ==Other media and entertainment== * [[Jabberwock (magazine)|''Jabberwock'' (magazine)]] * [[Jabberwock (play)|''Jabberwock'' (play)]] * [[Jabberwocks]], Brown University a cappella group * [[Jabberwocky (album)|''Jabberwocky'' (album)]], by Clive Nolan and Oliver Wakeman * [[Jabberwocky (musical)|''Jabberwocky'' (musical)]], by Andrew Kay, Malcolm Middleton and Peter Phillips * [[List of Better Off Ted episodes#ep12|"Jabberwocky"]], an episode of the TV series ''Better Off Ted'' * [[Jabbawockeez]], a dance group * Jabberwocky Graphix, media company owned by American artist [[Brad W.
